  <subsection>
    <title><xref ref="prog_gcdaslincomb"></xref></title>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          From <xref ref="prog_usingeuclid"></xref>,
          <m>\gcd ( {180, 126} ) = 18</m>.
          <me>
            \begin{aligned}18 \amp = 126 - 54 \cdot 2 \\ \amp = 126 - ( {180 - 126} ) \cdot 2 \\ \amp = 126 \cdot 3 + 180 \cdot ( { - 2} ) \end{aligned}
          </me>
          So <m>\gcd ( {180, 126} ) = 18</m>,
          and <m>18 = 126 \cdot 3 + 180 \cdot ( { - 2} )</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          From <xref ref="prog_usingeuclid"></xref>,
          <m>\gcd ( {4208, 288} ) = 16</m>.
          <me>
            \begin{aligned}16 \amp = 64 - 48 \\ \amp = 64 - ( {112 - 64} ) = 64 \cdot 2 - 112 \\ \amp = ( {176 - 112} ) \cdot 2 - 112 = 176 \cdot 2 - 112 \cdot 3 \\ \amp = 176 \cdot 2 - ( {288 - 176} ) \cdot 3 = 176 \cdot 5 - 288 \cdot 3 \\ \amp = ( {4208 - 288 \cdot 14} ) \cdot 5 - 288 \cdot 3 \\ \amp = 4208 \cdot 5 + 288 \cdot ( { - 73} ) \end{aligned}
          </me>
          So <m>\gcd ( {4208, 288} ) = 16</m>,
          and <m>16 = 4208 \cdot 5 + 288 \cdot ( { - 73} )</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
